rows.field_350778: Seeks major gifts from your largest and most loyal individual and corporate supporters, but also includes efforts to bring in smaller amounts from other donors.
Better when looking for companies willing to sponsor or underwrite our organization's programs or events, especially if our group's efforts align with the company's mission or values.
Raising money fast, putting out a call for donations that can quickly and easily attract donors who may be able to make gifts of all sizes. Better for unforeseen needs that require a quick response.
Door-to-door or phone solicitations are also great means to collect contact information from donors, volunteers, and special event attendees.
Securing grant funding involves identifying opportunities through grant-giving foundations and other organizations, then writing and submitting effective grant proposals.
Events themselves bring in money, and can also attract the attention of individuals who may donate additional funds or volunteer their time and talents to the organization.
Having a "click to donate" link on each page that goes directly to a page where people can contribute makes it easy for visitors to chip in while our nonprofit is on their minds.
